      <head>Baronin Bach</head>
      <div>

        <p>Aristocratic friend (perhaps pupil?) of Schenker.  </p>
          
          <p>She appears in Schenker's diaries first in 1907 being coached by Schenker in an
          aria from the <hi rend="italic">St. Matthew Passion</hi> (OJ 1/6, p. 35, July 13, 1907),
          and in 1908 (where her first name is abbreviated to "El.") she meets with Schenker's
          disapproval (OJ 1/8, p. 72, February 9, 1908). She features again in Schenker's diary for
          1913, inviting him to house concerts. There is no known correspondence between Baronin
          Bach and Schenker.</p>

      </div>
